1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:03,098
And get this,  predict what happens next.

2
00:00:03,048 --> 00:00:06,971
If you get it right, you're already thinking like a senior engineer.

3
00:00:06,971 --> 00:00:11,019
Each partition has a configurable replication factor (typically 3).

4
00:00:11,019 --> 00:00:16,028
One replica is the Leader — it handles all producer writes and consumer reads.

5
00:00:16,028 --> 00:00:20,923
The other replicas are Followers — they replicate data from the leader asynchronously.

6
00:00:20,923 --> 00:00:25,653
The set of followers that are fully caught up is called the ISR (In-Sync Replicas).

7
00:00:25,653 --> 00:00:30,740
Here's something nobody tells you: most production bugs at FAANG aren't code bugs.

8
00:00:30,740 --> 00:00:32,750
They're system design bugs.

